WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.437
(baby cooing)

00:05.573 --> 00:07.575
(baby babbles)

00:09.777 --> 00:11.779
(baby fusses)

00:15.449 --> 00:17.451
(baby grunts)

00:22.190 --> 00:24.192
*

00:26.727 --> 00:30.998
-(baby grunts)
-Oh.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.566
WOMAN:
I love you.

00:32.600 --> 00:35.703
-I love you, my beautiful boy.
-(baby coos)

00:40.608 --> 00:42.610
(baby grunts, fusses)

00:45.913 --> 00:48.116
WOMAN:
How long have you been gone?

00:48.149 --> 00:50.017
Days? Weeks?

00:50.050 --> 00:52.220
Wonder if you're--

00:53.454 --> 00:55.356
If I'm even here.

00:55.389 --> 00:57.258
Or if I'm there?

00:57.291 --> 00:59.293
-(clock chiming)
-Still?

01:00.328 --> 01:01.862
Remind me.

01:01.895 --> 01:03.864
(door opens)

01:03.897 --> 01:06.767
How long have you been gone?

01:06.800 --> 01:08.802
(door slams)

01:16.677 --> 01:18.679
(baby crying)

01:28.689 --> 01:30.658
(car door shuts)

01:30.691 --> 01:32.693
(car driving away)

01:34.762 --> 01:37.131
How did we find this place?

01:37.165 --> 01:40.000
A dream you made true.

01:40.033 --> 01:42.303
Or did you?

01:42.336 --> 01:44.638
In my head.

01:44.672 --> 01:46.940
Charles, are you still there?

01:46.974 --> 01:48.676
Here?

01:48.709 --> 01:50.278
-Inside me?
-(baby coos)

01:50.311 --> 01:52.313
(baby babbles)

01:54.848 --> 01:57.351
-(baby babbles)
-David.

01:57.385 --> 02:00.087
(David coos)

02:00.120 --> 02:02.190
WOMAN:
My beautiful boy.

02:04.992 --> 02:06.994
(David cooing)

02:17.037 --> 02:19.039
(muffled pulsing music)

02:31.552 --> 02:33.554
(music fades)

02:42.230 --> 02:44.632
(thunder rumbles)

02:44.665 --> 02:46.967
(insects trilling)

02:47.000 --> 02:49.002
WOMAN:
Days?

02:50.871 --> 02:53.374
Weeks?

02:53.407 --> 02:54.808
How long?

02:54.842 --> 02:56.577
I'm not sure.

02:56.610 --> 02:58.612
That's not an answer.

03:02.550 --> 03:04.084
(exhales)

03:04.117 --> 03:06.687
I found someone.

03:06.720 --> 03:08.556
Out there.

03:10.558 --> 03:12.560
Like me.

03:15.195 --> 03:18.031
I'm not alone.

03:18.065 --> 03:19.933
You were alone before?

03:23.136 --> 03:25.138
You know what I mean.

03:28.809 --> 03:31.612
-WOMAN: Where?
-Morocco.

03:31.645 --> 03:33.647
What?

03:35.949 --> 03:38.085
I won't be long.

03:38.118 --> 03:40.087
You said you weren't sure.

03:45.259 --> 03:47.261
-(bag thuds)
-Gabrielle.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.933
I have to go.

03:52.966 --> 03:55.736
I am coming back.

03:57.237 --> 03:58.439
(chokes back sob)

04:03.076 --> 04:05.078
(suitcases clicking shut)

04:06.780 --> 04:08.782
(insects trilling)

04:15.289 --> 04:17.291
(thunder rumbles)

04:23.931 --> 04:25.933
(muted disco music playing)

04:25.966 --> 04:27.635
VOICE:
Mommy.

04:29.637 --> 04:31.639
(lively disco music plays)

04:36.877 --> 04:38.879
(music stops)

04:44.151 --> 04:46.153
(clock chiming)

04:51.659 --> 04:53.661
(yawns)

05:02.503 --> 05:04.505
*

05:12.212 --> 05:14.214
(rainwater dripping,
birds singing)

05:18.251 --> 05:20.253
*

05:35.235 --> 05:37.237
*

05:50.283 --> 05:52.285
(quiet chatter)

05:55.756 --> 05:58.726
GABRIELLE:
"He didn't want to get lost
in the woods.

05:58.759 --> 06:02.029
"So he made a very small forest,
with just one tree in it.

06:02.062 --> 06:04.432
-It turned out to be
an apple tree."
-(David burbles)

06:04.465 --> 06:07.267
"The apples would be
very tasty, Harold thought,

06:07.300 --> 06:09.202
"when they got red.

06:09.236 --> 06:11.605
-So he put
a frightening dragon..."
-(David coos)

06:11.639 --> 06:13.641
"...under the tree
to guard the apples.

06:15.643 --> 06:18.612
"It was a terribly
frightening dragon.

06:18.646 --> 06:20.614
It even frightened Harold."

06:20.648 --> 06:22.349
(blows sharply)

06:22.382 --> 06:24.452
GABRIELLE:
"He backed away.

06:24.485 --> 06:26.754
"His hand holding
the purple crayon shook.

06:28.956 --> 06:30.824
"Suddenly he realized
what was happening.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.628
"By then...

06:34.662 --> 06:36.664
Harold was over his head."

06:48.141 --> 06:50.143
(machine whirring)

06:52.913 --> 06:55.048
(overlapping voices,
whining signals)

06:55.082 --> 06:58.218
(laughter, male voice speaking)

06:58.251 --> 07:00.220
(Farouk speaking
foreign language)

07:00.253 --> 07:02.255
(Farouk voice floating
over harsh buzzing)

07:20.674 --> 07:22.643
(speaking foreign language)

07:23.877 --> 07:25.879
(Farouk's voice echoing)

07:34.955 --> 07:37.858
*

07:45.799 --> 07:47.535
(growling)

07:50.804 --> 07:52.773
(fire crackling)

07:52.806 --> 07:56.209
DR. MONAHAN:
I will now read something.

07:56.243 --> 07:58.712
And I would like you
to tell me what,

07:58.746 --> 08:02.049
if anything, it means to you.

08:02.082 --> 08:04.084
Would that be agreeable?

08:05.553 --> 08:07.555
(telephone ringing
in next room)

08:09.422 --> 08:13.226
"Every man is born as many men

08:13.260 --> 08:16.697
and dies as a single one."

08:17.731 --> 08:19.600
Heidegger.

08:21.669 --> 08:24.972
Does this statement
hold meaning for you?

08:25.005 --> 08:27.608
Personal meaning?

08:32.345 --> 08:34.347
DR. MONAHAN:
What a waste.

08:38.218 --> 08:40.754
Perhaps move him to three.

08:40.788 --> 08:42.923
Oh, forget it.

08:42.956 --> 08:44.958
Useless lad.

08:52.566 --> 08:54.568
(door shuts)

08:56.403 --> 08:58.405
(muffled voices wailing,
speaking)

09:00.373 --> 09:02.375
(distant sirens)

09:09.650 --> 09:11.652
-(overlapping low chatter)
-(lively music plays quietly)

09:13.053 --> 09:14.454
NURSE:
Rest a bit.

09:28.969 --> 09:30.971
(wheelchair squeaking faintly)

09:37.611 --> 09:39.579
(distant clatter)

09:39.613 --> 09:41.615
(footsteps passing)

09:55.796 --> 09:57.798
(both chuckle)

10:00.133 --> 10:02.202
(sobbing)

10:12.379 --> 10:14.381
*

10:30.998 --> 10:33.000
(inhales deeply)

10:33.033 --> 10:35.035
(exhales)

10:45.813 --> 10:48.648
-(men shouting angrily)
-(air raid sirens blaring)

10:48.682 --> 10:51.284
(screaming, gunfire)

10:51.318 --> 10:53.821
(screams, shrill cacophony)

11:06.934 --> 11:08.368
Excuse me.

11:08.401 --> 11:10.070
Sorry.

11:10.103 --> 11:12.372
That woman there.

11:12.405 --> 11:14.574
Do you know where she came from?

11:15.608 --> 11:16.910
The camps.

11:20.948 --> 11:22.850
Any family?

11:22.883 --> 11:24.517
No one.

11:24.551 --> 11:27.487
Poor thing.

11:27.520 --> 11:29.522
Thank you.

11:36.363 --> 11:38.365
(insects trilling)

11:40.300 --> 11:42.302
("Wot!" by Captain Sensible
playing)

11:43.570 --> 11:45.773
*

11:45.806 --> 11:48.175
(music muffled)

11:48.208 --> 11:50.710
(music loud)

11:53.613 --> 11:54.948
* Bang! *

11:55.983 --> 11:57.985
* Bang! *

11:59.152 --> 12:01.154
(insects trilling,
exotic bird screeching)

12:04.124 --> 12:06.126
(sighs)

12:27.680 --> 12:29.682
(birds chirping,
insects trilling)

12:35.823 --> 12:37.825
(exotic bird crying)

12:39.026 --> 12:40.994
(bell tolling in distance)

12:41.028 --> 12:43.030
*

12:59.112 --> 13:01.114
(wood creaks)

13:05.485 --> 13:07.487
(plane passing overhead)

13:10.557 --> 13:12.559
(distant explosions)

13:18.298 --> 13:20.300
(footsteps scraping softly)

13:23.170 --> 13:25.172
(dirt crumbles)

13:40.220 --> 13:42.222
(cautious breathing)

13:52.065 --> 13:54.567
(breathing heavily, yelps)

13:54.601 --> 13:56.303
(Charles grunts)

13:56.336 --> 13:58.005
(both grunting)

14:00.040 --> 14:03.576
(both grunting, groaning)

14:08.681 --> 14:10.083
(choking)

14:12.886 --> 14:15.488
-(soldier grunting)
-CHARLES: Kill yourself.

14:15.522 --> 14:17.024
(echoing):
Kill yourself...
kill yourself...

14:17.057 --> 14:18.358
-Kill yourself...
-(Charles gasps for air)

14:18.391 --> 14:21.328
(gasping, coughing)

14:21.361 --> 14:23.363
-Kill yourself...
-(Charles panting)

14:24.965 --> 14:26.433
(gunshot)

14:28.468 --> 14:30.803
(panting)

14:40.113 --> 14:42.115
("Wot!" by Captain Sensible
fades in)

14:47.620 --> 14:50.857
* When I woke up this morning,
I was feeling fine *

14:50.890 --> 14:53.026
* But this cat starts banging,
man, what a swine *

14:53.060 --> 14:55.395
* So I called reception,
but to no avail *

14:55.428 --> 14:57.297
* That's why I'm telling you
this sorry tale... *

14:57.330 --> 14:59.332
(music continues, muffled)

15:01.068 --> 15:02.469
Do you hear something?

15:02.502 --> 15:04.504
(muffled beat)

15:07.941 --> 15:09.909
No.

15:09.943 --> 15:11.778
Huh.

15:11.811 --> 15:13.813
(music continues, muffled)

15:25.092 --> 15:27.060
(thunder rumbles)

15:27.094 --> 15:29.096
(beat continues)

15:31.831 --> 15:33.833
(thunder rumbles)

15:43.843 --> 15:45.912
(breathes deeply)

15:45.945 --> 15:47.947
(music grows louder)

15:56.323 --> 15:58.291
* Once a lifetime, twice a day *

15:58.325 --> 16:00.327
* If you don't work,
you don't get no pay *

16:00.360 --> 16:02.829
* I been to the east,
I been to the west *

16:02.862 --> 16:05.465
* But the girls I like best
are the ones undressed *

16:05.498 --> 16:07.667
* Well, hello, Adam,
where you been? *

16:07.700 --> 16:09.836
* I said a'stand aside,
'cause I'm feeling mean *

16:09.869 --> 16:12.639
* I've had a gutful of you
and I'm feeling bad. *

16:12.672 --> 16:14.674
(music stops)

16:14.707 --> 16:16.709
(insects trilling)

16:19.379 --> 16:21.381
*

16:28.721 --> 16:30.723
GABRIELLE:
David.

16:32.425 --> 16:34.827
My beautiful boy.

16:34.861 --> 16:37.664
(David fusses)

16:37.697 --> 16:39.699
GABRIELLE:
Who will you become?

16:43.836 --> 16:45.838
What will you do?

16:51.711 --> 16:53.846
Fall in love?

16:56.283 --> 16:57.417
Fight in a war?

16:57.450 --> 17:00.920
(screaming)

17:00.953 --> 17:02.622
Will you be content?

17:04.691 --> 17:07.594
Strong?

17:07.627 --> 17:09.629
Will you be like your father?

17:11.731 --> 17:14.434
A good shepherd?

17:15.468 --> 17:16.903
Or will you be like me?

17:18.938 --> 17:20.940
When will you learn the truth?

17:20.973 --> 17:22.909
(seagulls crying)

17:22.942 --> 17:25.545
That this world
is an ugly place.

17:28.815 --> 17:30.817
VOICE:
Mommy.

17:43.663 --> 17:45.398
Mommy.

17:54.241 --> 17:56.243
Mama.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.584
I'm right here.

18:04.617 --> 18:07.154
Your David, I'm here.

18:07.187 --> 18:10.123
I don't understand,
why can't she see me?

18:10.157 --> 18:11.824
SWITCH:
I don't know.

18:11.858 --> 18:14.761
I've never gone
this far back before.

18:22.802 --> 18:25.738
DAVID:
Farouk is coming,
I can feel it.

18:25.772 --> 18:28.074
Please, I have to warn her.

18:28.107 --> 18:29.509
Switch, do something.

18:29.542 --> 18:31.911
SWITCH:
I can't. I'm sorry.

18:31.944 --> 18:34.281
I don't know how much longer
I can keep us here.

18:34.314 --> 18:36.082
I'm so tired.

18:36.115 --> 18:37.684
Can't you use your power?

18:37.717 --> 18:39.252
DAVID:
I don't know.

18:39.286 --> 18:41.020
Mama!

18:43.022 --> 18:44.824
Mama, it's me, David.

18:44.857 --> 18:46.359
Your son.

18:46.393 --> 18:48.695
I'm grown now, from the future.

18:52.131 --> 18:54.667
You have to--
No, don't walk away.

18:54.701 --> 18:56.503
Mama.

18:56.536 --> 18:58.338
Come back.

19:00.240 --> 19:02.342
-SWITCH: What do we do?
-DAVID: I don't know.

19:02.375 --> 19:03.976
But we're running out of time.

19:18.258 --> 19:20.227
(quiet chatter)

19:20.260 --> 19:22.229
DAVID:
I don't understand.

19:22.262 --> 19:24.130
How are we here?

19:24.163 --> 19:26.533
So much earlier.

19:26.566 --> 19:28.235
SWITCH:
I don't know.

19:28.268 --> 19:30.102
These times are linked somehow.

19:32.339 --> 19:34.341
(pencil scratching)

19:37.844 --> 19:39.579
(blows sharply)

19:44.417 --> 19:47.420
Not too bad, right?

19:50.923 --> 19:52.692
No, I agree.

19:52.725 --> 19:55.595
Could be better.

19:55.628 --> 19:57.630
Could be... better.

20:04.404 --> 20:06.406
(exhales)

20:21.153 --> 20:23.122
(fire crackling)

20:23.155 --> 20:25.057
*

20:52.018 --> 20:53.720
(inhales deeply)

20:53.753 --> 20:55.755
(exhales slowly)

21:02.362 --> 21:04.331
(woman screaming, gunfire)

21:04.364 --> 21:06.366
-MAN: They're coming!
-(woman shouting)

21:11.638 --> 21:13.640
*

21:16.275 --> 21:18.244
(birds singing)

21:18.277 --> 21:22.014
DAVID:
Wow. This is how they met?

21:22.048 --> 21:24.083
My parents.

21:24.116 --> 21:26.853
In a mental hospital.

21:26.886 --> 21:28.755
SWITCH:
Why is that funny?

21:28.788 --> 21:30.923
DAVID:
I don't know,
I-I guess it just...

21:30.957 --> 21:32.959
runs in the family.

21:35.828 --> 21:37.196
Hi.

21:37.229 --> 21:39.198
(shouting in other room)

21:39.231 --> 21:41.534
Hi.

21:44.203 --> 21:46.473
(laughs)

21:48.508 --> 21:50.510
Nice day.

21:54.481 --> 21:56.315
Beautiful.

21:59.886 --> 22:01.521
Hungry?

22:03.690 --> 22:05.291
Yes.

22:05.324 --> 22:07.126
CHARLES:
Mm-mm-mm.

22:07.159 --> 22:09.796
Mmm.

22:09.829 --> 22:12.965
-I haven't had cherry pie
since before the war.
-(chuckles)

22:12.999 --> 22:15.802
(Charles exhales)

22:15.835 --> 22:19.539
Have you heard of a tomato?

22:19.572 --> 22:21.874
(laughs)

22:21.908 --> 22:23.676
Well, we say to-mah-to,
but, uh, yes.

22:23.710 --> 22:25.712
Hmm.

22:25.745 --> 22:28.481
Well, I'd never seen one before.

22:28.515 --> 22:30.817
And it's not an apple, you know.

22:30.850 --> 22:32.351
No.

22:32.385 --> 22:34.654
-But I thought it was an apple.
-(chuckles)

22:34.687 --> 22:37.156
-So I took a bite.
-(laughs)

22:37.189 --> 22:40.560
Did you see that
when you were in my mind?

22:41.928 --> 22:44.697
The tomato that is not an apple?

22:48.568 --> 22:50.102
I...

22:55.908 --> 22:58.411
There's a Greek word.
Telepathy.

22:58.445 --> 23:00.980
Which means "distant feeling
or perception."

23:03.049 --> 23:04.751
I have that skill.

23:04.784 --> 23:07.754
I don't know why.

23:07.787 --> 23:11.190
I can hear thoughts.
Memories.

23:11.223 --> 23:15.227
But it-it occurred to me
that there should be rules.

23:15.261 --> 23:18.831
-Mm.
-People deserve their privacy.

23:20.900 --> 23:23.703
So I don't pry
when I'm in there.

23:23.736 --> 23:27.740
I just... I try to help.

23:27.774 --> 23:30.376
Are there others like you?

23:30.409 --> 23:31.844
Maybe. I don't know.

23:34.647 --> 23:35.948
Do you think it's odd?

23:35.982 --> 23:38.217
(chuckles) A little.

23:38.250 --> 23:41.220
(both laugh)

23:41.253 --> 23:43.255
But I like odd.

23:48.094 --> 23:50.229
I'm not well, you know.

23:50.262 --> 23:52.699
Neither am I.

23:56.435 --> 24:00.006
I've seen blood on fire.

24:06.713 --> 24:08.147
We can change.

24:08.180 --> 24:10.917
People don't change.

24:10.950 --> 24:12.852
I don't believe that.

24:12.885 --> 24:15.321
That's sweet.

24:17.657 --> 24:20.259
-Do me a favor?
-Anything.

24:20.292 --> 24:24.130
When the time comes...
prove me wrong.

24:27.700 --> 24:30.803
("True Love Will Find You in the
End" by Daniel Johnston begins)

24:35.975 --> 24:40.547
* True love will find you
in the end *

24:43.382 --> 24:46.285
* You'll find out *

24:46.318 --> 24:49.756
* Just who was your friend *

24:52.058 --> 24:56.996
* Don't be sad,
I know you will *

25:00.366 --> 25:03.302
* But don't give up until *

25:03.335 --> 25:07.574
* True love will find you
in the end *

25:12.211 --> 25:16.348
* This is a promise
with a catch... *

25:17.416 --> 25:21.220
Ha! (laughs)

25:21.253 --> 25:23.355
* Only if you're looking *

25:23.389 --> 25:26.325
* Can it find you... *

25:26.358 --> 25:28.060
(laughs)

25:28.094 --> 25:30.897
-(Charles humming)
-* 'Cause true love *

25:30.930 --> 25:33.432
* Is searching, too *

25:36.903 --> 25:40.206
* But how can it recognize you *

25:40.239 --> 25:43.209
* If you don't step out
into the light *

25:43.242 --> 25:46.045
* The light *

25:46.078 --> 25:49.916
* Don't be sad,
I know you will *

25:53.285 --> 25:56.088
* Don't give up until *

25:56.122 --> 26:00.192
-(Gabrielle laughing)
-* True love will find you
in the end... *

26:00.226 --> 26:02.194
(Charles speaking indistinctly)

26:02.228 --> 26:04.230
*

26:25.284 --> 26:27.486
(insects trilling)

26:28.487 --> 26:30.489
*

26:45.337 --> 26:47.439
GABRIELLE:
You awake?

27:09.295 --> 27:12.464
-I had the most wonderful dream.
-Tell me.

27:15.534 --> 27:18.104
We lived far away from here.

27:18.137 --> 27:21.173
You and me. Together.

27:21.207 --> 27:25.712
And the stars...

27:25.745 --> 27:28.981
The belonged to us.

27:29.015 --> 27:32.051
Sounds nice.

27:36.322 --> 27:38.324
Just a dream.

27:43.930 --> 27:45.965
Doesn't have to be.

27:45.998 --> 27:49.201
We're in the madhouse.

27:50.236 --> 27:52.438
Until we're not.

27:55.007 --> 27:56.508
Say the word.

27:58.210 --> 28:01.080
(whispers):
There's something I can do.

28:01.113 --> 28:02.882
A trick?

28:07.186 --> 28:09.822
Well, in that case...

28:09.856 --> 28:11.891
what are we waiting for?

28:25.471 --> 28:27.439
-*
-(cheers and applause)

28:27.473 --> 28:30.076
("She's a Rainbow"
by the Rolling Stones playing)

28:44.390 --> 28:47.459
* She comes in colors
everywhere *

28:47.493 --> 28:50.296
* She combs her hair *

28:50.329 --> 28:53.099
* She's like a rainbow *

28:53.132 --> 28:56.803
* Coming, colors in the air *

28:56.836 --> 28:58.537
* Oh, everywhere *

28:58.570 --> 29:01.740
* She comes in colors *

29:04.844 --> 29:08.080
*

29:25.664 --> 29:28.935
* She comes in colors
everywhere *

29:28.968 --> 29:30.937
* She combs her hair *

29:30.970 --> 29:34.673
* She's like a rainbow *

